<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF207-214-466  </DOCNO><DOCID>07 214 466.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Communications  April 1989 v12 n2 p69(11).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>ODA: a document architecture for open systems. (Office DocumentArchitecture) (technical)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Hunter, Roy; Kaijser, Per; Nielsen, Frances H.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The main concepts and aims of the new ISO 8613 standard -generally referred to as Office Document Architecture - that hasbeen jointly published by the International Organization forStandardization and the Consultative Committee on InternationalTelephone and Telegraph, is described here.andP;  ODA provides ageneral information architecture which can be used as a basis forencoding documents so that they can be transferred betweendissimilar document processing systems.andP;  The architecture supportsthe representation of multi-media documents (containing text,raster graphics and computer graphics) in both revisable and finalforms.andP;  ODA is expected to have a significant role in theintegration of office systems, particularly those that operate inan Open Systems Interconnection environment.andP;  (Reprinted bypermission of the publisher)andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     CommunicationOffice AutomationInformation SystemsDocument DeliveryDocument PreparationOSI Standard.andO;Feature:   illustrationchart.andO;Caption:   Two views of a document's structure. (chart)Document processing model outline. (chart)Hierarchical logical structure. (chart)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>